<div class="format_text" id="comment-body-29590">
<p>@Nandan &#8211; Excellent contribution, thank you. You&#8217;re quite right that spreadbetting can be used to remain exposed to a stock despite the 30day rule. I&#8217;d remind readers to read up in detail about spreadbetting, as novices often gear up much more than they think they do when using a spreadbet, and that spreadbetting can lose you a lot of money if you don&#8217;t know what you&#8217;re doing. But for a sophisticated investor looking to use his or her CGT allowance, this is indeed another useful tool in the armory.</p>
</div>
