					<dd class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
<div class="format_text" id="comment-body-30078">
<p>@Andy &#8211; also worth noting that there is a free CGT uplift on death so the entire estate becomes liable for IHT, but not CGT. This means, each asset is classed as if it is purchased for it&#8217;s value on the date of death. Original purchase values are then ignored.</p>
<p>Someone has mentioned telling your relative to sell these assets &#8211; this isn&#8217;t always viable, especially for those of pensionable age. You may find she is drawing income from such assets. </p>
<p>Good luck.</p>
</div>
					</dd>
