					<dd class="comment byuser comment-author-investor bypostauthor even thread-even depth-1">
<div class="format_text" id="comment-body-35838">
<p>@Aury &#8211; We&#8217;re lucky in the UK with the <a href="http://monevator.com/2009/11/10/how-uk-dividends-are-taxed/" rel="nofollow">tax treatment of dividends</a>. In fact, if you&#8217;re a lower rate taxpayer you don&#8217;t pay extra tax on the dividends you receive at all. Higher rate payers effectively pay 25%, which is less than the higher rate of tax. For a while with CGT at 18% it made sense to go for capital gains here, but if CGT is going to rise to 40% or more (still in dispute) then income products may get more popular again.</p>
<p>Just realised I&#8217;ll probably have to overhaul and re-write this whole page when we have the new CGT rules. Curse the politicians! <img src='http://monevator.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif' alt=';)' class='wp-smiley' /> </p>
</div>
