<div class="format_text" id="comment-body-42810">
<p>@David &#8211; I&#8217;m not qualified to give personal tax advice and so this isn&#8217;t that, but I believe in general that&#8217;s the case, yes. However, you&#8217;d have had to declare the capital loss on your tax return for 09/10 in order to now set it against your capital gain this year.</p>
<p>Please also note that as I write (9th August 2010) this article needs to be updated in light of the annoying changes in the recent emergency budget, which has lifted CGT for higher rate taxpayers to 28%. The general principles of CGT avoidance remain the same (if anything they&#8217;re even more important now!)</p>
<p>Thanks for the kind words about the site.</p>
</div>
